-- French Electric Vehicle Sales Fail to Take Off, Les Echos Says
-- B y   A n d r e w   R o b e r t s
-- 2012-05-22T05:51:45Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-22/french-electric-vehicle-sales-fail-to-take-off-les-echos-says.html
Sales of electric cars in France
reached 1,594 in the first four months of 2012, accounting for
less than 0.2 percent of the automobile market,  Les Echos 
reported, citing Mediterranean electric car association  Avem .  Car manufacturers expect electric vehicles to account for
between 5 percent and 10 percent of French sales by 2020,  Les
Echos  said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Andrew Roberts  in Paris at 
 aroberts36@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Celeste Perri at   cperri@bloomberg.net . 